<title type="html"><![CDATA[Burned Mapper 0 game, getting gray screen]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=991&amp;p=8546#p8546"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Quietust wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Yes, that would indeed be a problem - NES-NROM-128 is only designed to handle 16KB of PRG ROM, and you're trying to give it 32KB.<br /><br />CPU A14 would normally go to pin #27 on the ROM - try cutting the current trace and then running a wire from the cart edge (you'll probably need to shave off the solder mask at the end of the pad) to pin 27 on the PRG ROM.<br /></div><br /><br />    I should have figured that out in the first place. I studied my Mario 1 cart and noticed it routed that pin to a different place on the connector, so I soldered a wire from pin 27 of the ROM to pin 41 of the connector. It works!<br /><br />    I like how I don't have to worry about the sprite mirroring switch (since the game doesn't HAVE any sprites).<br /><br />    Also, what's a good method for stripping off the solder mask?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=292">Computolio</a> — Tue Jan 24, 2006 11:06 pm</p><hr />
