<title type="html"><![CDATA[Burned Mapper 0 game, getting gray screen]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=991&amp;p=8523#p8523"><![CDATA[
Yes, that would indeed be a problem - NES-NROM-128 is only designed to handle 16KB of PRG ROM, and you're trying to give it 32KB.<br /><br />CPU A14 would normally go to pin #27 on the ROM - try cutting the current trace and then running a wire from the cart edge (you'll probably need to shave off the solder mask at the end of the pad) to pin 27 on the PRG ROM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Tue Jan 24, 2006 1:59 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
