<author><name><![CDATA[Computolio]]></name></author>
<updated>2006-01-24T13:32:04-07:00</updated>
<published>2006-01-24T13:32:04-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=991&amp;p=8522#p8522</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=991&amp;p=8522#p8522"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Burned Mapper 0 game, getting gray screen]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=991&amp;p=8522#p8522"><![CDATA[
So as an extremely late celebration of <a href="http://andorejr.chaseheadquarters.net/archives/00000182.html" class="postlink">Bokosuka Wars Awareness Month</a>, I decided to use my new EPROM burner to put the game on a real NES cart. I found a Mapper 0 (NROM board)-based game (Baseball), and swapped out the mask ROMs for EPROMS I had burned. <br /><br />    I used uCON64 to split the .NES ROM into .PRG and .CHR files, and then burned one onto a 27C256 and the other onto a 27C64 EPROM.<br /><br />    So I put the whole mess back together and am getting a gray screen. At this point I think I picked out the wrong donor board, as it's an NROM-128 and apparently games with 32k PRG should use an NROM-256. Any way I can fix this without having to start over?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=292">Computolio</a> — Tue Jan 24, 2006 1:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
